title: Archaeologists discover 2,300-year-old massacre frozen in time
description: Archeologists have uncovered evidence of an Iron Age massacre in the ancient town of La Hoya in northern Spain's Basque Country.

title: Rockets strike Iraqi base where US troops are located, US defense official says
description: Six rockets landed near Erbil International Airport in the semiautonomous Kurdistan region in northern Iraq on Wednesday, according to a statement released by the Ministry of Interior of the Kurdistan Regional Government.

title: 'Ask somebody!': CNN correspondent blasts Trump's Proud Boys denial
description: CNN's Sara Sidner responds to President Trump's claim that he does not know who the Proud Boys are a day after encouraging the far-right group to "stand back and stand by" during the first presidential debate.

title: Heiress sentenced to nearly seven years in Nxivm case
description: Clare Bronfman, heiress to the Seagram liquor fortune, was sentenced to 81 months in prison Wednesday -- more than the 60-month sentence prosecutors had recommended.

title: These brands promised to get rid of their racist logos. Here's why it's taking so long
description: It's been more than three months since Aunt Jemima, Uncle Ben, Cream of Wheat and several other food companies made national headlines by acknowledging the racist origins of some of their brand mascots and announcing plans to change them.

title: Greenland's ice sheet melting as fast as any time in last 12,000 years
description: We've known for some time now that Greenland's ice sheet is melting at an alarming rate.

title: Comey knocks Barr's attacks on the Russia probe: 'I have no idea what on Earth he is talking about'
description: Former FBI Director James Comey faces off with Senate Republicans on Wednesday over the FBI's 2016 Russia investigation in a hearing that's being held fewer than six weeks before the 2020 presidential election.

title: 'Inshallah': Biden lights up Twitter with Muslim phrase
The pandemic could push an alarming number of women out of the workforce
description: First the good news: There are more women in senior-level positions across corporate America.

title: The first known person to be cured of HIV has died of cancer
description: After a five-month battle with leukemia, the first known person to be cured of HIV has died of cancer, according to the International AIDS Society.

title: Tractor runs over and kills woman sleeping on beach
description: A woman sleeping on a beach in Oceanside, California, has died after being run over by a piece of construction equipment, police told CNN.

title: Around 40% of the world's plant species are threatened with extinction
description: Some 40% of the world's species of plants are threatened with extinction, the Royal Botanic Gardens Kew says in a new report.

title: Van Jones describes the debate moment that upset him
description: • 'Sh*tshow': See CNN hosts' blunt reaction to debate

title: The International Space Station has an air leak
description: Astronauts on the International Space Station (ISS) have successfully narrowed down the source of a small air leak that had been growing in size.

title: Late-night comedy reacts to first presidential debate
description: Late-night hosts mocked the chaotic first presidential debate between President Donald Trump and democratic rival Joe Biden.

title: Free diving 112 meters into the depths
description: Arnaud Jerald broke the world record for the deepest sea dive in bi-fins at a depth of 354 feet. Now, in a dive lasting three minutes and 24 seconds, he's surpassed his own record, descending to almost 367.5 feet.

title: There is no getting 'back to normal,' experts say
description: As 2020 slides into and probably infects 2021, try to take heart in one discomfiting fact: Things are most likely never going "back to normal."

title: Japan's biggest military budget in decades
A photographer's unsettling portrait of post-industrial America
description: Gregory Crewdson is a creature of habit. "I try to do almost the exact same thing each day," he said from his home in Becket, Massachusetts, explaining that his routine is structured down to the food he eats. Each morning, the photographer wakes up early to travel to a picturesque and remote pond in the Berkshires, accessible only through the Appalachian Trail. "I ritualistically make time during the summer months to do long-distance swims," he said. "That, to me, is central to my existence."

title: The world's 50 best foods
description: "There is no love sincerer than the love of food," George Bernard Shaw said. Judging by the number of amazing dishes out there, he was right.
